    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><persName><name ref="Adalgisus">Adalchisi</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Priests"><name ref="Albo">Alboni</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbitero</rs> germani filii <persName>bonę memorie
                                <name ref="Alchis">Alchisi</name></persName> permutano beni con
                            <persName ref="#people/3305" key="#Bishops">Hieremia</persName> gratia
                        Dei huius sancte Lucane ecclesie humilis <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs>
                        (…). Adalchisi e Alboni presbitero cedono ad parte <rs key="#Churches"
                            >ecclesie</rs> vestre <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/231">Sancti Terentii</orgName>, sita in
                            <placeName ref="#places/587" key="#Churches">vico Elingo</placeName>,
                        qui est de sub potestate ipsius <rs key="#Mother_churches">episcopatui</rs>
                        vestri <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/68" key="#Mother_churches">Sancti
                            Martini</orgName>, idest una petia de terra, quas habemus in loco ubi
                        vocitatur <placeName key="#Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#places/473">Campora</placeName>, et est <rs key="#Confinia"
                            >tenente ipse terra uno caput</rs> in terra nostra qui supra germani,
                        quas nobis reservamus, et in aliquantulo in terra <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/201"
                            key="#Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Mother_churches">Sancti
                            Petri de <placeName ref="#places/52" key="#Mother_churches"
                                >Roma</placeName></orgName>, et alio caput tene similiter in terra
                        nostra qui supra germani, lato uno tenet in terra <persName
                            ref="#people/225" key="#Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions"
                            >Hildeprandi</persName>, et alio lato tene in terra suprascripti
                            <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/201"
                            key="#Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions">Sancti Petri</orgName>;
                        petia ipsa de terra (…) quod est per mensura ad iuxta pertica mensurata <rs
                            key="#Size">sistariorum sidecim et dimidium</rs> (…). Ricevono in cambio
                        una petia de terra in <placeName ref="#places/64"
                            key="#Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention #Roads"
                            >Vico Asulari</placeName>, pertenentes suprascripte <rs key="#Churches"
                            >ecclesie</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/231">Sancti
                            Terentii</orgName> et <rs key="#Confinia">est tenente ipsa terra uno
                            caput</rs> in <rs key="#Roads">via publica</rs>, alio caput tenet in <rs
                            key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Mention">terra domni
                            regi</rs>, lato uno tene in terra qui fuit <persName>quondam <name
                                ref="Teudebertus">Teutperti</name></persName>, et alio lato tene in
                        terra nostra qui supra germani; petia ipsa de terra (…) quod est per mensura
                        ad iuxta pertica mensurata <rs key="#Size">sistariorum quattordecim</rs>
                        (…). Ubi et super hanc comutationem secundum legem tu qui supra <persName
                            ref="#people/3305">Hieremia</persName> episcopus direxisti <rs
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities">misso tuo</rs>, idest
                            <persName key="#Witness #Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Deacons"
                                ><name ref="Garipertus">Gheriperto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Deacons">diaconus</rs>, et <persName ref="#people/1514"
                            key="#Marquis/duke">Adalbertus</persName> dux <rs
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities">misso suo</rs>, idest
                            <persName key="#Witness #Notary #Missus_of_other_public_authorities"
                                ><name ref="Teobaldus">Teutpaldus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>, qui ambulaverunt et previderunt adque
                        renuntiaverunt vobis, qualiter meliorata comutationem dedimus ad parte
                        suprascripte ecclesie, quam recepissemus, ut magis omni tempore stabilem
                        persistant. Pena in duplum. (…) <persName key="#Writer #Notary"><name
                                ref="Adalfredus">Adalfridi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> scrive due <rs key="#Commutatio"
                            >cartulas</rs>. Actum <placeName ref="#places/4"
                            key="#Mother_churches #Bishops">Luca</placeName>.</ab>
                    <ab>Oltre ai due missi sottoscrivono altri sei <rs key="#Witness"
                        >testimoni</rs>. Le firme riconoscibili però sono solo quelle di <persName
                            key="#Witness #Notary"><name ref="Adalbertus"
                            >Adalpertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Teobaldus">Teopaldo</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Scabini"><name ref="Teofridus">Teufridi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Scabini">scabinus</rs> e di un sconosciuto <persName
                            key="#Witness #Notary">[…]d[...]</persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>.</ab>
                </div>
